latestPosts.caption:
I had the incredible opportunity to attend a workshop at @metaindia , where I got to meet and learn from amazing people in the industry. 🌟

But to be honest, it wasn’t all smooth for me. 😅 It was a challenge to manage those nerves, but I reminded myself that growth happens when we step out of our comfort zone.

I’m incredibly grateful for this opportunity, and I know I wouldn’t have gotten here without the support of my amazing audience. 🙏💖 Every like, comment, and message motivates me to keep pushing forward, learning, and growing as a creator. This journey wouldn’t be possible without you all, and for that, I’m truly thankful. ❤️

Here’s to more growth, more learning, and more incredible opportunities ahead. 

#GratefulHeart #ContentCreator #MetaWorkshop #ThankYou

latestPosts.caption:
🦢 Just a girl and her black saree moment.🖤

“Did you know the fabric I’m wearing was born in Paris?
This is georgette — named after French dressmaker Madame Georgette de la Plante in the early 1900s.
Originally silk, it’s known for its lightness, flow, and timeless elegance.
Today, it’s draped in sequins and reimagined as the modern saree. Fashion fades, but fabric tells stories.”
